\@writefile{lof}{\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {1}{\ignorespaces \textbf  {Probabilistic forecasting head and output comparison.} The latent representation $\mathbf  {z}$ from the backbone is processed by a probabilistic parameterisation module that produces the forecast mean $\hat  {\mu }$ and variance $\sigma ^{2}$. The mean path undergoes $K{=}50$ MC-Dropout forward passes to estimate epistemic uncertainty, while the learned variance captures aleatoric uncertainty. Both are combined into a total uncertainty estimate. The bottom row contrasts deterministic forecasting (point prediction), probabilistic forecasting (aleatoric bands), and uncertainty-aware forecasting (decomposed aleatoric and epistemic bands).}}{2}{}\protected@file@percent }
\newlabel{fig:forecasting_head}{{1}{2}{}{}{}}
